**First thought**

If someone would have solved dp questions earlier, then the first things that comes to mind after looking at the question structure is to apply dp.
It seems similar to **fractional-knapsack** as well as **0-1 knapsack**.

Thanks to [@priyavratuniyal09](https://leetcode.com/priyavratuniyal09/) and [@Gaurav_Kungwani_](https://leetcode.com/Gaurav_Kungwani_/) for pointing it out!

**Why dp is unncessary here?**

This is simply because, when you apply dp, then there is **different cost** associated on the choice of each type of element.
But, here no matter what you can pick any element and the cost you have to pay for that is **only 1**. That is upon picking 1 box, the truckSize reduces by 1 only.

It is not like, on picking a box will cost you 5 spaces(big size) in truck, while other will cost only 1 space(small size).

**Approach**

So, apply greedy instead after sorting it in descending order to maximize the chances of the units you gain.

I hope I have made all your doubts clear. If there is any further query, do not shy to comment!

