This question is regarding the 2 sum problem. The logic is just that we will need to check the sum of a,b such that a+b == 2^n eg : 2 = 1+1, 4 = 2+2, 8 = 5+3
Also we can use the complexity be n for traversing each element in array but the inner loop is for checking with the sum such that in [1,3] map stored with 1:1 now again in for loop we can check the 2^0 - 2^21 inclusively - the element at the point. 
Which we can actually use as constant of inner loop as in thr question it is given that delicious[i] value will be from 0 to atmost 2^21, so we can count complexity as O(n*22).

Also in the question we need to keep modding with 1000000007

