**Synopsis:**

Use a map `m` to track the frequency of each value `x` in `A`.  Then accumulate the count `cnt` of good meals to be returned via a brute-force search for `y` such that `x + y == t` where `t` is a power of 2 between [2<sup>0</sup> .. 2<sup>21</sup>] inclusive.

---

**Contest 222 Screenshare:**

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/484fc798-efa5-41ed-8aec-5a43c4a2a200_1609720619.4969242.png)

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jPTjegnxYp4

* My solution TLE'd because I mis-read the problem: I thought 10<sup>20</sup> was the max value for `deliciousness[i]` (but it's actually 2<sup>20</sup>) 😕

