**Understand the problem**
1.  You need to make pairs which are powers of 2
2.  Generate a list of powers of 2
3.  Iterate each item in the arr and check if the other item in the pair exists in the map
4.  If found, increment the count

```
class Solution {
    public int countPairs(int[] arr) {
        List<Integer> pows = new ArrayList<>();
        int pow = 1;
        for (int i = 1; i < 32; i++) {
            pows.add(pow);
            pow = pow * 2;
        }

        int count = 0;
        Map<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        for (int num: arr) {
            for (int p: pows) {
                int diff = p - num;
                if (map.containsKey(diff) && diff >= 0) {
                    count += map.get(diff);
                    count %= 1000000007;
                }
            }
            map.put(num, map.getOrDefault(num, 0) + 1);
        }
        return count;

    }
}
