# Approach
Just straightforwardly count the number of occurrences of every distinct meal deliciousness, and then calc the number of pairs that form the powers of 2 by multiplying the occurrences of each element.
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N * 22) == O(N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(N)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int countPairs(std::vector<int>& data) {
        int modulo = 1e9 + 7;
        std::unordered_map<int, int> counts;
        long long result = 0;

        for (auto d: data) {
            counts[d]++;
        }

        for (const auto& it: counts) {
            for (int i = 1, pow2 = 1; i <= 22; i++, pow2 *= 2) {
                const auto& correspIt = counts.find(pow2 - it.first);

                if (correspIt == counts.end() || it.first > correspIt->first) {
                    continue;
                }

                if (it.first == correspIt->first) {
                    result += (long long)(it.second - 1) * (it.second) / 2;
                } else {
                    result += (long long)(it.second) * correspIt->second;
                }
                result %= modulo;
            }
        }

        return result;
    }
};
```

