# Intuition
Any good meal has exactly tow items. I could get this can be solved in O(n)2. So tried to optimize.

# Approach
Any two numbers from input make the good meal. So if I have a number in hand, I can look for all the possible pair from map upto the max possible value.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(22powerN) -> 22 is constant -> So O(N)

- Space complexity:
O(N) - every number from input array will be placed in Map

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int countPairs(int[] deliciousness) {
        int MOD = 1_00_00_00_007;
        int res = 0;
        Map<Integer, Integer> numVsCount = new HashMap();

        for(int num : deliciousness) {
            // The max number given in the input is 2power20. And any good meal has exactly two item. 
            // So while adding two of the same max number would result in a number less than 2power22. 
            // This is just a max number I have considered to have an upper limit.
            for(int i = 0; i <= 22; i++) {
                int k = (int)Math.pow(2, i);
                if(numVsCount.containsKey(k - num)) {
                    res += numVsCount.get(k - num);
                    res %= MOD;
                }
            }
            numVsCount.put(num, numVsCount.getOrDefault(num, 0)+1);
        }

        return res;
    }
}
```

