# Approach
1. We will traverse all the aray from left to the right with 1st cut position.
2. For each 1st cut position we hafe to find possible 'left' second cut position and 'right' second cut position.
3. To do so we will use binary search.
4. To use BS we need to constract a sum array, keeping track on every sum accumulated for every index.
5. Difference between 'left' and 'right' positions for second cut is an addition for the task answer for current first cut position.
6. We will update the sum in modulo while traversing the array. I use a seperate function for it for convenience/readability only.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O( n*log(n) )

- Space complexity: O(n)

