# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Sum of Subarray -> prefixSum, then binary search the potential min max pivot that can form leftSum <= midSum <= rightSum  

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. We can just use the origin array to form a prefix array to avoid extra space complexity.  
2. During a linear scan leftSum = `prefix[i]`, midSum = `prefix[mid] - leftSum`, *Here always remember don't use perfix[left] because left is changing during your binary search and leftSum is fixed*. You can get rightSum with the same approach easily.  
3. Move pivot  
- If we wanna get the shortest midSum, when we have a correct answer, move right index to left  
- If we wanna get a largest midSum, move left to right

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n log n)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(1)

